
∴ rvm use [ruby-string]

Setup current shell to use a specific ruby version.


For a list of currently install ruby string please run

  ∴ rvm list

For creating gem if not existing:

  ∴ rvm --create 1.9.2@funky

For creating project .rvmrc file:

  ∴ rvm --rvmrc 1.9.2@funky

Above commands can be also combined for best experience:

  ∴ rvm --rvmrc --create use 1.9.2@funky
  Using /home/mpapis/.rvm/gems/ruby-1.9.2-p290 with gemset funky

Do not forget to check to generated .rvmrc file - it contains usefull comments.


Please see documentation for further information:

  http://rvm.beginrescueend.com/rvm/basics
